<h3>Course Description</h3>


In the spirit of Felix Klein's <i>Erlanger Programm</i>, this course
surveys Mobius, hyperbolic, elliptic, projective and absolute geometries
as compared to and contrasted with Euclidean geometry.  In addition to
the development of mathematical skills, the course seeks to build
analytical skills in <b>reading</b> and clarity of expression in
<b>writing</b>.


<h3>Prerequisites and Requirements Met</h3>

MAS 202, MAS 222, and MAS 251

<h3>Text and Materials</h3>

<ul>
<li>Michael Henle, <i>Modern Geometries</i>, 2nd edition
</ul>

